	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yes it's possible. The RetroUSB MMC1 board will make your job easier as you will only need to get someone to program your ROM file to a ROM chip and then you just solder all the components onto the RetroUSB MMC1 board. The components would be the ROM chip and two RAM chips, one for CHR-RAM and one for the WRAM (save ram). Also it's likely you could have someone else handle putting the whole thing on the cartridge for you if you pay for their time and all the materials involved.

		

